items.title: Peanut Butter Chocodilla
method: Melt 2 tsp butter or ghee and place 1 tortilla on top
Spread peanut butter on tortilla
Drizzle with honey and add chocolate chips
Allow chocolate chips to melt, then mix with peanut butter using spoon to smear
Place second tortilla on top and continue to toast until bottom tortilla is golden brown
Remove from heat and cut into four triangles
Let melt and flip tortilla and toast other side

items.title: Salmon Coconut Milk Bisque
ingredient: 2 cups salmon, grilled, separated into bite-sized chunks
method: Prepare garlic, roasted red pepper, leeks, grilled salmon and red pepper flakes. Divide into two portions
Saute 1 portion of above ingredients in pot with oil of choice (I used grapeseed oil), about 5 minutes
Add veggie broth, coconut milk to pot and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently
Add ½ of salmon bits to pot and blend with immersion blender (alternatively use regular blender and put back in pot)
Add lemongrass, paprika, and 2nd portion of prepared garlic, roasted red pepper, leeks, and red pepper flakes
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently
Add parsley and remaining salmon until heated through
Serve and garnish with parsley and paprika

items.title: Sweet Potato Brownies
ingredient: 2/3 cup sweet potato puree(about one small potato)
method: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Butter an 8-inch square pan; set aside. In a medium saucepan over low heat, melt butter. Remove pan from heat, and stir in cocoa. Let cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt, then stir in sugar and sweet-potato puree, then egg. Add vanilla to cocoa mixture.

Add flour mixture to cocoa mixture and stir until no traces of flour remain. Spoon into prepared pan; smooth the top. Bake until surface of brownies looks barely dry and a knife inserted 2" from the edge comes out with a few moist crumbs, about 20 minutes.

Technically you should probably let them cool to room temperature before serving, but I recommend using a plastic knife to cut them if you want to cheat and cut while still warm! (necessary if eaten with ice cream).
